text: Prunus incisoserrata (, meaning "sharp-toothed flowering cherry") is a species of Prunus native to central China, preferring to grow at 1100–2900m. It is a shrub reaching a height of 2–5m. On Huangshan Mountain it is found growing beneath Prunus clarofolia and alongside fellow shrubs Symplocos paniculata, Hydrangea chinensis, Neillia hanceana, Morus australis and Kerria japonica.http://powo.science.kew.org/taxon/urn:lsid:ipni.org:names:77108490-1 ==References== ==External links== incisoserrata Category:Endemic flora of China Category:Plants described in 2010
